climbs.name: Alien Jesus
climbs.fa: Sam Duke, Dalton MacNeil and Caleb Mazurkiewicz

content.description:
Take the path of least resistance up the face. Crux comes after clipping the second bolt, while traversing left towards better holds.This route moves very close to its neighbor on its left. Follow the bolts through a few more fun moves to the top. 



Start just left of the low ledge for Stains blue and Golden Teachers. 

5 bolts. Rap rings.

climbs.name: Augmented Reality
climbs.fa: F. Côté, E. Côté, C. Mazurkiewicz 2021

content.description:
Excellent movement with a powerful crux.

Pull up to a small crater. Move up and left into the aesthetic left-angling feature.



Right side of Creek wall, the right side of the blank looking wall and just left of a double overhang.

4 bolts. Rap rings

climbs.name: Clarity
climbs.fa: F. Côté, E. Sloan 2020

content.description:
Start on the far left of the blank overhanging wall and follow the obvious system of seams and features that diagonal up and right across the face. 

A crux awaits when the seam turns horizontal. Harder than it looks.



Starts on the far left of the blank overhanging wall.

5 bolts

climbs.name: Controversial Cubensis
climbs.fa: F. Côté, E. Côté 2020

content.description:
Start by the permanent seeping spot (wet holds can be avoided) and crimp up to good holds. Navigate a fun technical slab to a slanting ramp then continue up to a small corner and seam to finish at a set of cold shuts.



Starts by a spot of permanent seeping.

7 bolts, cold shuts

climbs.name: Earle
climbs.fa: Greg Hughes and Caleb Mazurkiewicz

content.description:
Large features and jugs make this fun.



Start is directly below a large hole in the rock that has a couple of cool underclings.

3 bolts, rap rings

climbs.name: Ellis D.
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz , François Côté and Eric Sloan

content.description:
Climb up the less than vertical face through several overlaps. This route offers a bouldery crux, nice rests and great rock. 



Located on the main section of the creek wall. It is to the left of Im a Amanita and right of One with the Universe.

8 bolts and rap anchor

climbs.name: Ergot
climbs.fa: F. Côté, E. Sloan, F. Corbett 2020

content.description:
A fun little climb. Start on the large ramp, reach a jug and clip the somewhat high first bolt. Pull past a small overlap onto the face and up to better holds. Make your way to the right end of a diagonal crack and up the final face to a nice ledge.



Near the far right of Creek area. The face immediately right of the angular overhangs.

4 bolts, rap rings

climbs.name: Flying Saucers
climbs.fa: Greg Hughes, Shawn Bethune, Emily Keast and Cheryl Karthaus

content.description:
Cruxy bottom, juggy middle and a fun finish.



Just left of One with the Universe and right of a grassy ramp at head height.

6 bolts, rap rings

climbs.name: Hot for Golden Teachers
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz and Kyle Landry

content.description:
Start up on easy terrain to a ledge just off the ground below several alcoves. Follow bolts though alcoves to the top.



On the right side of the creek wall locate alcoves. This route starts by climbing to small ledge 4-6ft off of the ground. 

4 bolts and rappel rings

climbs.name: I'm an Amanita
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz and Nicole Thorne

content.description:
Fun climbing with a few technical moves that will leave you with a smile on your face. 



Bolted line just left of the large tree at the creek wall.

10 bolts to a tree anchor.

climbs.name: LIBERTY
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz and Kyle Landry

content.description:
Start by standing on a stump or get a boost. Stick clipping is advised if this is at your limit. Pull a couple committing moves to good holds and a small ledge. Move off the ledge gaining face holds and balance your way up past the bolts. Pull one more move to stand on final ledge, clip the chains. 



Located near the right end of the creek wall. This route finishes to the right of the small head wall at the top of the cliff. 

7 bolts and bolted anchor.

climbs.name: Magic Tea
climbs.fa: Dalton MacNeil,  Caleb Mazurkiewicz and Sam Duke

content.description:
Climb the short seam that offers fun movement and a committing crux just before the top. 



Found at the creek wall, left of the gully and right of Hot for Golden Teachers. The anchor is visible from the ground, located just left of tree on ledge above.

3 bolts. Rap rings.

climbs.name: Micro-Dose
climbs.fa: Greg Hughes and Joe Kennedy, November, 2020

content.description:
Reach up and yard on a big jug then launch for a good crimp below the first bolt. Make a tricky move to gain a narrow ledge then unlock the final sequence to the top. 



Just right of Stoned Ape and about 25 feet left of Flying Saucers.

3 bolts, bolted anchor

climbs.name: One with the Universe
climbs.fa: F. Côté, M. Klompmaker, C. Mazurkiewicz

content.description:
From the jug at head height, pull onto the slab and climb up trending slightly right to better holds. Pull up to some jugs and continue up aiming for the middle of the roof. Tricky move pulling the roof!



starts about 15 ft left of the lowest point on Creek Wall, at an obvious jug at head height.

7 bolts, rap rings

climbs.name: Penis Envy
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz and François Côté

content.description:
Start on nice jugs and move up on to a slabby face. After getting established on the face use small holds and footwork to make your way to the chains. "Not for the timid or easily offended."



Directly in front of the large tree at the base of the creek wall locate an incut jug. This route is to the right of Im a Amanita. 


7 bolts. Rap rings.

climbs.name: Philosopher's Stone
climbs.fa: Greg Hughes, Dalton Scott and Caleb Mazurkiewicz

content.description:
Nice rock, cool movement along the flake.



This is the first route on the far left hand side of Creek Wall. It lies very close to the approach trail for the west side of the cliff.

3 bolts, rap rings

climbs.name: Pink Buffalo
climbs.fa: Caleb Mazurkiewicz, Gregory Hughes and Dalton Scott

content.description:
Start by pulling the first lip on your left using incut crimps. Once on the lip move right onto a slightly higher ledge. From here you can clip the first bolt.* if you are a shorter climber or this is at your limit stick clipping might be wise.* High first bolt is due to rock quality (hollow flake). Move up the weaknesses through a few technical moves using jugs, underclings, sidepulls and more jugs.



Creek wall far right. This route is located on the right end of the overhanging wall that that houses "Clarity 5.13c". Look for a high first bolt just as the lip at the bottom of the wall ends.

4 bolts Rap rings

climbs.name: Stains Blue
climbs.fa: Kyle Landry and Caleb Mazurkiewicz

content.description:
Start by gaining the ledge, either mantle or move right on easier terrain. Clip first bolt from jugs and the fun begins. Climb up following bolts to the top.



Start near a ledge on the right side of the creek wall. To the left of Hot for Golden Teachers.

4 bolts and rap rings

climbs.name: Stoned Ape Theory
climbs.fa: Greg Hughes and Joe Kennedy, November, 2020

content.description:
A fun little route that starts out with easy climbing and then quickly packs a punch.



Left side of Creek Wall between Earle and Flying Saucers.


3 bolts, bolted anchor

climbs.name: Synesthesia
climbs.fa: F. Côté, E. Côté, C. Mazurkiewicz 2021

content.description:
Climb up a short tricky face (often wet) to an inset slab and overhang. Continue more easily to the second overhang. Pull a tricky mantle and continue up the easy face above.



Near the right side of Creek Wall. This route climbs the double overhangs.

5 bolts, rap rings
South facing wall gets lots of sun with some shaded belays. Wall seeps early season. Rock type : Pink granite
